name: Buffalo Ranch Green Bean Fries
author: Nelena Brown
summary: These lightened-up green beans fries are crisp, crunchy, and totally satisfying. Refrigerate any leftovers.
ingredients: 1 pound green beans, stem ends trimmed, rinsed
directions: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C)
Line a baking sheet with foil and grease with nonstick spray
Place flour in a shallow bowl
Whisk 1/2 cup Buffalo sauce and eggs together in a small mixing bowl
Combine bread crumbs and ranch mix in a third bowl
Dredge green beans in flour, dip in the egg mixture, then coat with the bread crumbs
Set out on the prepared baking sheet
Roast in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 12 minutes
Serve immediately with remaining Buffalo sauce for dipping
